711947f-a.title: Manhattan: 29th Street - 11th Avenue
711947f-a.text:
29th Street, north side, west from and including Eleventh Avenue.
January 28, 1932.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

710613f-b.title: Manhattan: 11th Avenue - 29th Street (West)
710613f-b.text:
11th Avenue, west side, north from W. 29th Street. At the left
are the remains of a 2-story planing mill. View 2 shows the demolition
period of same. This is at the N. W. corner of 29th Street. In the
background is a 5-story tenement (No. 319 Eleventh Aenue) at the
N. W. corner of 30th Street. This has disappeared in the later view.
Its site would be just behind the foreground aUto.
January 28, 1932
May 12, 1930
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTI NS

711945f-a.title: Manhattan: 29th Street (West) - 11th Avenue
711945f-a.text:
29th Street, north side, east from 539 West 29th, east of Eleventh
Avenue. The houses in the foreground have been condemned by
Tenement House Commissioner Langdon Post. In the distance gleams
the new Parcel Post Office, which replaced the New York Central
milk sheds.
May 30, 1934.
..  P. L. Sperr.
